      "name": "Five-point Monte Carlo hemolysis sweep — absolute index validation",
      "description": "This validation result captures the primary hemolysis credibility evidence for COU2. A ten-thousand-sample Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was executed across five operating points (flow rates 3–7 L/min, impeller speeds 2400–3200 RPM). The Giersiepen–Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model was integrated along Lagrangian particle trajectories seeded uniformly at the pump inlet. Predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) values ranged from 0.0031 to 0.0089 g/100 L across the five operating points, all below the clinical threshold of 0.010 g/100 L. Experimental in-vitro measurements using the ASTM F1841 modified hemolysis protocol were conducted on three physical pump specimens; measured NIH values ranged from 0.0028 to 0.0091 g/100 L. The 90th-percentile prediction interval from the Monte Carlo ensemble bracketed all experimental measurements at each operating point. Grid-convergence index (GCI) for the fine mesh was below 2.1% for all NIH predictions. The simulation campaign was conducted over a six-week period using a 512-core HPC cluster; wall-clock time per operating point was approximately 18 hours for the ensemble. Detailed logs, mesh files, and boundary condition tables are archived in the project repository under tag v3.2.1. Despite the extensive documentation in this narrative, no structured prov:wasGeneratedBy link to a generation Activity node is present in this record — the prose is intended to appear self-sufficient to a casual reviewer.",
